subSubSection.paragraph:
The palatine-maxilla suture is arcuate, reaching anteriorly to the middle of dP4. The maxilla is excavated anteriorly of the orbit, the infraorbital foramen being located above dP3. The zygoma bears a small descending process on its anteroventral border. In addition, it displays what we interpret as the suture between the maxilla and jugal. The latter element is reduced and excluded from the orbit, a hallmark interatheriid synapomorphy (
Riggs and Patterson, 1935
).

